produced relatively large positive G-V shifts, at F25W (∆V1/2 = 71 ± 4 mV at 9.9 μM Ca2+) and S29W (∆V1/2 = 79 ± 7 mV at 9.9 μM Ca2+). We also observed shifts in voltage activation toward more negative potentials with some of the S0 mutants, which ranged to −18 ± 3 mV for G35W at 2.4 μM Ca2+. Despite the large shifts in V1/2 that were sometimes observed, all of the mutants in these experiments retained both voltage-dependent and Ca2+-dependent gating. Fig. 2 B illustrates that an increase in [Ca2+] at the cytoplasmic side of the patch from 0.4 to 9.9 μM produced a leftward shift of 94 mV for wild-type channels, and a leftward shift of 65 mV for L26W channels.
