6 A). Similarly, a decrease in D overpredicted the G-V shift observed at nominally 0 Ca2+, while a decrease in zJ both overpredicted the G-V shift for 0 Ca2+ and underpredicted the G-V shift observed for 13 μM Ca2+
for this mutant (Fig. 6 B). Finally, changing only the Ca2+ sensor parameters C or KD by an amount sufficient to produce the large G-V shifts observed with L26W predicted a striking decrease in Ca2+ dependence
